{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":755,"text":"In my early days as a graduate student,"},{"time":2794,"text":"I went on a snorkeling trip\noff the coast of the Bahamas."},{"time":6789,"text":"I'd actually never swum\nin the ocean before,"},{"time":9762,"text":"so it was a bit terrifying."},{"time":12016,"text":"What I remember the most is,\nas I put my head in the water"},{"time":15040,"text":"and I was trying really hard\nto breathe through the snorkel,"},{"time":19314,"text":"this huge group\nof striped yellow and black fish"},{"time":24704,"text":"came straight at me ..."},{"time":26817,"text":"and I just froze."},{"time":28975,"text":"And then, as if it had\nsuddenly changed its mind,"},{"time":32612,"text":"came towards me\nand then swerved to the right"},{"time":35073,"text":"and went right around me."},{"time":36920,"text":"It was absolutely mesmerizing."},{"time":38470,"text":"Maybe many of you\nhave had this experience."},{"time":41239,"text":"Of course, there's the color\nand the beauty of it,"},{"time":44685,"text":"but there was also\njust the sheer oneness of it,"},{"time":47637,"text":"as if it wasn't hundreds of fish"},{"time":50004,"text":"but a single entity\nwith a single collective mind"},{"time":53163,"text":"that was making decisions."},{"time":55666,"text":"When I look back, I think that experience\nreally ended up determining"},{"time":59372,"text":"what I've worked on for most of my career."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64157,"text":"I'm a computer scientist,"},{"time":65461,"text":"and the field that I work in\nis artificial intelligence."},{"time":68639,"text":"And a key theme in AI"},{"time":70180,"text":"is being able to understand intelligence\nby creating our own computational systems"},{"time":74647,"text":"that display intelligence\nthe way we see it in nature."},{"time":78467,"text":"Now, most popular views of AI, of course,\ncome from science fiction and the movies,"},{"time":82929,"text":"and I'm personally a big Star Wars fan."},{"time":86501,"text":"But that tends to be a very human-centric\nview of intelligence."},{"time":91144,"text":"When you think of a fish school,"},{"time":93375,"text":"or when I think of a flock of starlings,"},{"time":96352,"text":"that feels like a really different\nkind of intelligence."},{"time":100945,"text":"For starters, any one fish is just so tiny"},{"time":104882,"text":"compared to the sheer size\nof the collective,"},{"time":107793,"text":"so it seems that any one individual"},{"time":110927,"text":"would have a really limited\nand myopic view of what's going on,"},{"time":113944,"text":"and intelligence\nisn't really about the individual"},{"time":116302,"text":"but somehow a property\nof the group itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120118,"text":"Secondly, and the thing\nthat I still find most remarkable,"},{"time":123373,"text":"is that we know that there are no leaders\nsupervising this fish school."},{"time":129163,"text":"Instead, this incredible\ncollective mind behavior"},{"time":132688,"text":"is emerging purely from the interactions\nof one fish and another."},{"time":137244,"text":"Somehow, there are these interactions\nor rules of engagement"},{"time":141236,"text":"between neighboring fish"},{"time":143015,"text":"that make it all work out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145736,"text":"So the question for AI then becomes,"},{"time":148411,"text":"what are those rules of engagement\nthat lead to this kind of intelligence,"},{"time":152593,"text":"and of course, can we create our own?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":154999,"text":"And that's the primary thing\nthat I work on with my team in my lab."},{"time":158943,"text":"We work on it through theory,"},{"time":160604,"text":"looking at abstract rule systems"},{"time":162976,"text":"and thinking about\nthe mathematics behind it."},{"time":165897,"text":"We also do it through biology,\nworking closely with experimentalists."},{"time":170579,"text":"But mostly, we do it through robotics,"},{"time":172556,"text":"where we try to create\nour own collective systems"},{"time":176484,"text":"that can do the kinds of things\nthat we see in nature,"},{"time":179215,"text":"or at least try to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181907,"text":"One of our first robotic quests\nalong this line"},{"time":184735,"text":"was to create our very own colony\nof a thousand robots."},{"time":189140,"text":"So very simple robots,"},{"time":190498,"text":"but they could be programmed\nto exhibit collective intelligence,"},{"time":194125,"text":"and that's what we were able to do."},{"time":196194,"text":"So this is what a single robot looks like."},{"time":198250,"text":"It's quite small,\nabout the size of a quarter,"},{"time":200797,"text":"and you can program how it moves,"},{"time":203131,"text":"but it can also wirelessly\ncommunicate with other robots,"},{"time":206571,"text":"and it can measure distances from them."},{"time":208762,"text":"And so now we can start to program\nexactly an interaction,"},{"time":212262,"text":"a rule of engagement between neighbors."},{"time":214713,"text":"And once we have this system,"},{"time":216631,"text":"we can start to program many\ndifferent kinds of rules of engagement"},{"time":220071,"text":"that you would see in nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221601,"text":"So for example,\nspontaneous synchronization,"},{"time":224601,"text":"how audiences are clapping\nand suddenly start all clapping together,"},{"time":229863,"text":"the fireflies flashing together."},{"time":234919,"text":"We can program rules\nfor pattern formation,"},{"time":237634,"text":"how cells in a tissue"},{"time":239444,"text":"determine what role\nthey're going to take on"},{"time":241570,"text":"and set the patterns of our bodies."},{"time":245045,"text":"We can program rules for migration,"},{"time":247158,"text":"and in this way, we're really learning\nfrom nature's rules."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250595,"text":"But we can also take it a step further."},{"time":253266,"text":"We can actually take these rules\nthat we've learned from nature"},{"time":256282,"text":"and combine them and create\nentirely new collective behaviors"},{"time":260100,"text":"of our very own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261960,"text":"So for example,"},{"time":263462,"text":"imagine that you had\ntwo different kinds of rules."},{"time":266374,"text":"So your first rule is a motion rule"},{"time":268517,"text":"where a moving robot can move\naround other stationary robots."},{"time":272882,"text":"And your second rule is a pattern rule"},{"time":274717,"text":"where a robot takes on a color\nbased on its two nearest neighbors."},{"time":278679,"text":"So if I start with a blob of robots\nin a little pattern seed,"},{"time":282148,"text":"it turns out that these two rules\nare sufficient for the group"},{"time":285078,"text":"to be able to self-assemble\na simple line pattern."},{"time":289114,"text":"And if I have more\ncomplicated pattern rules,"},{"time":291682,"text":"and I design error correction rules,"},{"time":294023,"text":"we can actually create really,\nreally complicated self assemblies,"},{"time":297144,"text":"and here's what that looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299874,"text":"So here, you're going to see\na thousand robots"},{"time":302883,"text":"that are working together\nto self-assemble the letter K."},{"time":306369,"text":"The K is on its side."},{"time":308223,"text":"And the important thing\nis that no one is in charge."},{"time":310978,"text":"So any single robot is only talking\nto a small number of robots nearby it,"},{"time":315827,"text":"and it's using its motion rule\nto move around the half-built structure"},{"time":319788,"text":"just looking for a place to fit in\nbased on its pattern rules."},{"time":323794,"text":"And even though no robot\nis doing anything perfectly,"},{"time":328216,"text":"the rules are such that we can get\nthe collective to do its goal"},{"time":331900,"text":"robustly together."},{"time":334033,"text":"And the illusion becomes\nalmost so perfect, you know --"},{"time":337039,"text":"you just start to not even notice\nthat they're individual robots at all,"},{"time":340479,"text":"and it becomes a single entity,"},{"time":342186,"text":"kind of like the school of fish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348013,"text":"So these are robots and rules\nin two dimensions,"},{"time":350776,"text":"but we can also think about robots\nand rules in three dimensions."},{"time":354111,"text":"So what if we could create robots\nthat could build together?"},{"time":358576,"text":"And here, we can take inspiration\nfrom social insects."},{"time":362189,"text":"So if you think about\nmound-building termites"},{"time":364873,"text":"or you think about army ants,"},{"time":366949,"text":"they create incredible,\ncomplex nest structures out of mud"},{"time":371226,"text":"and even out of their own bodies."},{"time":374602,"text":"And like the system I showed you before,"},{"time":376846,"text":"these insects actually\nalso have pattern rules"},{"time":379840,"text":"that help them determine what to build,"},{"time":381902,"text":"but the pattern can be made\nout of other insects,"},{"time":384228,"text":"or it could be made out of mud."},{"time":387178,"text":"And we can use that same idea\nto create rules for robots."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392221,"text":"So here, you're going to see\nsome simulated robots."},{"time":395406,"text":"So the simulated robot has a motion rule,"},{"time":397913,"text":"which is how it traverses\nthrough the structure,"},{"time":400270,"text":"looking for a place to fit in,"},{"time":402291,"text":"and it has pattern rules\nwhere it looks at groups of blocks"},{"time":405315,"text":"to decide whether to place a block."},{"time":408644,"text":"And with the right motion rules\nand the right pattern rules,"},{"time":411731,"text":"we can actually get the robots\nto build whatever we want."},{"time":416197,"text":"And of course, everybody wants\ntheir own tower."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419350,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":422000,"text":"So once we have these rules,"},{"time":423708,"text":"we can start to create the robot bodies\nthat go with these rules."},{"time":426898,"text":"So here, you see a robot\nthat can climb over blocks,"},{"time":430231,"text":"but it can also lift and move these blocks"},{"time":432936,"text":"and it can start to edit\nthe very structure that it's on."},{"time":436617,"text":"But with these rules,"},{"time":437789,"text":"this is really only one kind of robot body\nthat you could imagine."},{"time":441292,"text":"You could imagine\nmany different kinds of robot bodies."},{"time":443895,"text":"So if you think about robots\nthat maybe could move sandbags"},{"time":448529,"text":"and could help build levees,"},{"time":451102,"text":"or we could think of robots\nthat built out of soft materials"},{"time":455427,"text":"and worked together\nto shore up a collapsed building --"},{"time":459095,"text":"so just the same kind of rules\nin different kinds of bodies."},{"time":464210,"text":"Or if, like my group, you are completely\nobsessed with army ants,"},{"time":468457,"text":"then maybe one day we can make robots\nthat can climb over literally anything"},{"time":472855,"text":"including other members of their tribe,"},{"time":475053,"text":"and self-assemble things\nout of their own bodies."},{"time":478137,"text":"Once you understand the rules,"},{"time":479842,"text":"just many different kinds\nof robot visions become possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486792,"text":"And coming back to the snorkeling trip,"},{"time":489050,"text":"we actually understand a great deal\nabout the rules that fish schools use."},{"time":494769,"text":"So if we can invent\nthe bodies to go with that,"},{"time":497629,"text":"then maybe there is a future"},{"time":499081,"text":"where I and my group will get to snorkel\nwith a fish school of our own creation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508850,"text":"Each of these systems that I showed you"},{"time":511003,"text":"brings us closer to having\nthe mathematical and the conceptual tools"},{"time":515304,"text":"to create our own versions\nof collective power,"},{"time":518709,"text":"and this can enable many different kinds\nof future applications,"},{"time":521734,"text":"whether you think about robots\nthat build flood barriers"},{"time":524922,"text":"or you think about robotic bee colonies\nthat could pollinate crops"},{"time":529243,"text":"or underwater schools of robots\nthat monitor coral reefs,"},{"time":532791,"text":"or if we reach for the stars\nand we thinking about programming"},{"time":535918,"text":"constellations of satellites."},{"time":538148,"text":"In each of these systems,"},{"time":539784,"text":"being able to understand\nhow to design the rules of engagement"},{"time":543355,"text":"and being able to create\ngood collective behavior"},{"time":545893,"text":"becomes a key to realizing these visions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550742,"text":"So, so far I've talked about\nrules for insects and for fish"},{"time":554873,"text":"and for robots,"},{"time":557266,"text":"but what about the rules that apply\nto our own human collective?"},{"time":560866,"text":"And the last thought\nthat I'd like to leave you with"},{"time":563320,"text":"is that science is of course itself"},{"time":565025,"text":"an incredible manifestation\nof collective intelligence,"},{"time":568533,"text":"but unlike the beautiful\nfish schools that I study,"},{"time":571875,"text":"I feel we still have a much longer\nevolutionary path to walk."},{"time":576746,"text":"So in addition to working on improving\nthe science of robot collectives,"},{"time":581374,"text":"I also work on creating robots\nand thinking about rules"},{"time":584675,"text":"that will improve\nour own scientific collective."},{"time":588198,"text":"There's this saying that I love:"},{"time":589890,"text":"who does science\ndetermines what science gets done."},{"time":594239,"text":"Imagine a society"},{"time":597204,"text":"where we had rules of engagement"},{"time":598879,"text":"where every child grew up believing\nthat they could stand here"},{"time":602206,"text":"and be a technologist of the future,"},{"time":604652,"text":"or where every adult"},{"time":606177,"text":"believed that they had the ability\nnot just to understand but to change"},{"time":610320,"text":"how science and technology\nimpacts their everyday lives."},{"time":614820,"text":"What would that society look like?"},{"time":618386,"text":"I believe that we can do that."},{"time":619918,"text":"I believe that we can choose our rules,"},{"time":622233,"text":"and we engineer not just robots"},{"time":624014,"text":"but we can engineer\nour own human collective,"},{"time":626634,"text":"and if we do and when we do,\nit will be beautiful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630492,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631667,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}